The paper focuses on the development of a human-machine interface for remote training of robot tasks, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of vision-based 3D hand detection and gesture recognition, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning for remote research on massive robot farms, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and systems and control (cs.SY).
